node.text:
Our @usaf_thunderbird_maintainers have completed their first-ever local conversion of an F-16 Fighting Falcon, Tail Number A91-0470.

This process saved time, money, and manpower as well as reduced the completion time by more than 100 days.

For years the maintenance team has had the capabilities to convert a traditional gray F-16 to a Thunderbirds F-16 and in October 2020, the team moved forward with that effort.

An enlisted maintenance team was developed and assigned to the project with one mission... to convert 470.

212 days later, on May 5, 2021, they succeeded.

node.title: Thunderbirds accelerate change with first-ever F-16 conversion

⁣
It also served as our final mission for #AmericaStrong. It was an honor to partner with the @usnavyblueangels to salute frontline responders across the U.S. during this difficult time in our nation. ⁣
⁣
Stay healthy and stay tuned for team updates! ————————————————⁣

node.text:
Today we had the honor of flying 
Hometown Hero, Captain Peter Hempfling!

Peter is a US Army Veteran and career firefighter who’s worked at the Lakewood Fire Department for 30 years. Recently he and his team were awarded commendations from Cleveland Clinic EMS Leadership for their heroic actions.

In December 2020, Hempfling and his team responded to a call for a pregnant woman who was unconscious and seizing. When on scene, he used his 30 years of experience to treat and transport her.  Both the mother and the child survived thanks to Hempfling and his teams’ quick thinking. 

Thank you to Peter and Lakewood Emergency Services! We loved giving a little Thunderbird appreciation to you who give so much to make this world a better place!

Another one!

We're almost done with completing our second in-house conversion of another F-16 to join our fleet!

#dyk all our jets go through an extensive conversion program primarily consisting of replacing the ammo drum and cannon with a smoke oil tank and compressor, mounting a stopwatch to the HUD, installing a smoke system line and nozzle, and, most importantly, giving them a shiny new red, white, and blue paint job!
